title: For Sale/Trade:  Beretta CX4 Storm in .40 S&W plus 900 Rounds!!!
postcontent:
I have a Beretta CX4 Storm in .40 S&W with exactly 20 rounds through it and a little over 900 rounds that I want to trade for another CX4 Storm in 9mm (I am trying to get one that my wife will shoot, and she won't shoot anything larger than 9mm.  Don't ask me - it's a girl thing.)  

I originally posted this stating 600 rounds, but I miscounted the boxes (they are in a military surplus ammo can, and I didn't unpack them, I though I knew how deep the stacks were).  

Here is a breakdown on the ammo:

750 of the 900 rounds are Remington UMC (15 50-Round boxes)

1 50-Round Box Remington Golden Saber Bonded Brass-Jacketed Hollow Point (for when you REALLY want to put them down!)

1 50-Round Box Union Metallic Cartridge Company

1/2 50-Round Box Speer Lawman Gold Dot HP

1 50-Round Box Speer Lawman (Regular)

Yeah, I know.  It adds up to more than 900 rounds, but I didn't want to do a complete count and I know that there is at least 900 rounds, so I figured anything more than 900 would be a bonus for whoever gets it.

I can buy a Cx4 Storm in 9mm for 735.00, so I would let it all go for that much, or just trade me your 9mm Storm.  I did the math on the ammo and it is worth about $270 alone.  

I have had other people say, "Cx4 Storms are going for (whatever) dollars, so you should sell yours to me for that price." to which I reply, "Great!  Go buy one and let's trade!"  I am not really counting the ammo in the value of the rifle, I am just using it to get someone to either trade me rifles or buy mine for what I would have to pay for a 9mm one.  

If you want to trade, contact me and we can set up a time and place to meet.  Thanks, and I hope to hear from you soon!

  - Curtis

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom 5.45x39 AK-74 Bullpup (PRICE DROP)
postcontent:
Will take $1000 cash, or trade for a Beretta Cx4, Golani/Galil rifle, or a Daewoo DR200.

This gun began life as a Nodak spud NDS-2 5.45x39mm AK rifle.  With the help of a gentleman on the east coast, I've converted it into a bullpup rifle that cuts it close at 27.5" overall (legal minimum is 26").  The rifle now has quad rails, extremely sturdy as they are supported by the receiver where the lower handguard would be, the gas tube where the upper handguard would be, and the rear sight base.  Also has a vertical foregrip mounted on the lower rail, giving it a very comfortable AUG-like feel with the dual pistol grips.  The rifle feels very comfortable and points naturally, and is well-balanced.  I can easily aim and shoot this with one hand, and I am not a very strong guy.  Also, the safety lever has been machined out to allow for a bolt hold-open.  This is the only change that is irreversible, and it can be undone by simply replacing the lever for ten bucks.

Rifle will come with black Magpul BUIS (real ones, not the shitty PTS version), seven surplus polymer mags with steel lugs and lips, and 520 rounds of 7n6 surplus ball ammo.  Rifle will not include the Surefire G2X pictured, unless you specifically ask for it.

Will also include spare dust cover.

Will come with box with paperwork and nylon case that S&W includes to carry the gun and an extra mag. These only come with 1 mag however I have another factory mag that runs 20 bucks. Included with sale is almost 200 rds of ammo with half being hollow points and hydra-shocks and the other FMJ. Have ran 75 rounds out of this with no ftf or fte (25 were hp's to ensure reliability to carry them for defense). Reliable and actually really accurate for a .380. Serial number puts manufature date in march this year. Have called around local shops in Springfield to see how much they are going for now and the cheapest I could find was Loftis for 369.00 and they would have to see if could order it in just like any other place in Springfield area. They are sold out. So cheapest just for the gun is around 400.00 after tax. This gun is light weight and weighs less than a can of soda. Would prefer cash but open to trades. Not sure of what I want as I have or have had just about everything I wanted to try. If you are a gun nut like me you know the feeling and is why you are reading this :). Those of you who dont know much about the .380 round it is just a shortened 9mm. 9mm is 9x19 and .380 is 9x17. usually 15-20 grain difference in bullet so is still as affective as a 9mm in my opinion. This has a polymer frame with a stainless slide and barrel so really resistant to corrosive material that cause most guns to rust.  Reason for sale/trade, well I am a 1911 fan by heart. Figured would try this pocket gun but feel naked carrying it so back to the 3 lb 1911. Anyway questions just send me an email. 400.00 is the cash price which includes all factory stuff, 200 rds of ammo and an extra mag. Ammo is worth about 75 bucks alone and again 20 plus tax for the mag if you can get them right now. Kinda scarce with the pocket pistol craze this summer. Thanks and please include phone number and pics of your trade.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Daewoo DH40
postcontent:
Have a beautiful little gun that I'm looking for trades on, won't see too many of these babies floating around.

.40 S&W, Chromed Barrel, steel construction, DA/SA and a VERY cool "tri-action" system.

The tri-action essentially allows for the hammer to be laid down for carry, but with a near-instant return to single-action upon trigger pressure. For an example, see this video: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P89vfQUJVCQ

Very accurate little gun (I'm much more accurate with this than I am my M&P or Kahr), with an absolutely amazing trigger pull in single-action.

This has been a great winter carry piece, but with the pickup of a new Kahr for summer carry, I'm itching to trade for something new.

title: For Sale:  Ruger P89 9mm in EXCELLENT Condition
postcontent:
Ruger's P89, like all P-series pistols, were designed with the main goal - to produce high quality, reliable and affordable service and personal defense pistols.

The P89 was introduced by Ruger in 1991 to overcome design flaws and accuracy issues with its predecessor, the P85, and remained in production till just a few years ago.

Internally, the P89 is a recoil operated, locked breech semi-automatic pistol. It uses SIG-Sauer P220 type locking, when one massive barrel lug locks into large ejection port on the slide; The P89 utilizes a Browning-style tilting barrel: It also uses a battle-proven and reliable M1911 style link system.

This P89 features a Double action with decocker (the firing pin is locked by means of the internal safety that is actuated unless the trigger is pulled all the way back). It can also be fired using single action.

The P89 frame is made from aluminum alloy. The slide is made from stainless steel on this model. Grip panels are made from polymer, and an aftermarket Hogue grip is included in the sale.

Sights are dovetailed and have white dots for increased visibility.

All P-series pistols are extremely sturdy, capable of continuous firing of high-pressure +P loads without any damage to the firearm. They are often referred to as "built like tanks" for their reliability over many years.

The gun has been fired fewer than 200 rounds in its lifetime, and is in like-new condition. Included in the sale are two (2) factory high-capacity magazines.

Price: $350 or best offer.

Buyer to pay additional fees and/or costs, if any.

Call 303-three seven eight-8161

Email: icpilot_at_yahoo_dot_com
